CatDescriptText: Cutline of related image published in Pittsburgh Courier newspaper, December 1, 1945, pg. 15 reads: "Eating Their Cake Too - The seventy-fifth anniversary celebration of St. James AME Church, East End, was held Thursday evening. The youngest member, Morris Gaddie, and the second oldest member cut the five-tier birthday cake with 200 candles.  The cake was later cut and given to those who lighted candles in memory of loved ones.  Prominent Pittsburghers were guests. - Harris Photo."
TitMainTitle: Two elderly women wearing hats, lighting candles on five tiered cake, in St. James AME Church, for seventy-fifth anniversary, seen from altar
